.SH NAME
octane-cache-key - Print the cache key hash for a story ID


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBoctane cache key  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
key prints the SHA-256 hex digest octane uses as the cache key
for the given story ID with placeholder values for the remaining
key components (CSMS endpoint, story content, parameters).

.PP
This is useful for locating cached entries on the filesystem or
for debugging cache invalidation behaviour.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for key


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--cache-dir\fP=""
	override the cache directory (default: $XDG_CACHE_HOME/octane/cache)

.PP
\fB--config\fP="octane.yml"
	path to octane.yml configuration file

.PP
\fB--no-cache\fP[=false]
	bypass the result cache entirely

.PP
\fB-v\fP, \fB--verbose\fP[=false]
	enable verbose output


